Media organizations such as magazines, radio, and television have always relied on advertising to subsidize their operations. For print media, such as newspapers and magazines, advertising allowed them to deliver their product at a reasonable price for the consumer. Back when television and radio were over-the-air and free to the consumer advertising made it possible for those services to be provided for free. What is interesting to me is that according to According to [Adweek](https://www.adweek.com/performance-marketing/adedit-balancing-act-111116/) the number of ads in a given publication has not changed over time, holding steady at around a 50:50 mix of content to advertising. This 




Advertising is an important source of revenue for virtually every media organization. It is also an important source of revenue for the creator community. By itself, I have no real problem with advertising because I understand its importance. 